# Frontend Component Rules

## Component Pattern
- Server Components by default
- Add "use client" ONLY for: event handlers, hooks, browser APIs
- Co-locate: component.tsx, component.test.tsx in same directory
- One component per file, named export matching filename

## Data Fetching
- RSC: fetch data in Server Components, pass as props
- Client: TanStack Query with tRPC for dynamic data
- NEVER useEffect for data fetching
- Prefetch in RSC: `queryClient.prefetchQuery()`

## Forms
- Use React 19 useActionState + server actions
- Validate with Zod on both client AND server
- Show inline validation errors, not alerts
- Disable submit button while pending

## Styling
- Tailwind v4 utility classes only
- shadcn/ui for all UI primitives (Button, Input, Card, Dialog, etc.)
- Use `cn()` utility for conditional classes
- Mobile-first: design for 360px+ first, then scale up
- Dark mode: use CSS variables from shadcn theme

## Accessibility
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Use semantic HTML (button, nav, main, section, article)
- All images need alt text
- Form inputs need labels (visually hidden is OK)
- Exam interface: support keyboard shortcuts (A-D for options, arrows for nav)
